value.value: A cell projection part that is a branch of a unicellular trichome.

definition.value: Unicellular trichome (PO:0025537) is a trichome(PO:0000282) that is a single plant cell (PO:0009002). For a cell that forms a branch of a multicellular trichome, see multicellular trichome branch cell (PO:0025163).

value.value: A tubular cell projection that is part of a pollen tube cell and extends from a pollen grain.

definition.value: Carries the male gametes to into or near the ovule. May be branched in gymnosperms. This term replaces the obsolete term PO:0006345. Part of pollen tube cell (PO:0025195).

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the biosynthesis of deoxyribose phosphate, the phosphorylated sugar 2-deoxy-erythro-pentose.
The process of loading nitrate into the sieve tube or companion cell of the phloem for long distance transport from source to sink.
Catalysis of the reaction: malonate + ATP + coenzyme A = malonyl-CoA + AMP + diphosphate.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of malonate, the propanedioate ion.
Binding to a brassinosteroid.
The directed movement of molybdate ions out of the vacuole.
Catalysis of the reaction: 7-hydroxymethyl chlorophyll a + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+ chlorophyll a + 2 oxidized ferredoxin + H2O.
Enables the transfer of nicotinate from one side of a membrane to the other.
Enables the transfer of N-methylnicotinate from one side of a membrane to the other.
Initiation of a region of tissue in a plant embryo that is composed of one or more undifferentiated cells capable of undergoing mitosis and differentiation.
Enables the transfer of thiamine pyrophosphate a substance from one side of a membrane to the other.
A phytochelatin metabolic process in which a metal is incorporated with phytochelatin to form a complex.
A phytochelatin metabolic process in which a metal and exogenous sulfur are incorporated with phytochelatin to form a complex.

The epithelial cell differentiation process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an acinar cell, a secretory cell that is grouped together with other cells of the same type to form grape-shaped clusters known as acini.
A process of actin filament bundle distribution that results in the compaction of actin filaments.
Any process that starts the inactive process of meiosis.

The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the perianth over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The perianth is a collective phyllome structure composed of two or more petals, sepals, or tepals.
Catalysis of the reaction: caffeoyl-CoA + a saturated primary alcohol = an alkyl caffeate + CoA.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of ester derivatives of alkyl caffeate.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + myristic acid + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + myristoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + palmitic acid + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + palmitoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + oleic acid + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + oleoyl-CoA.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location within a nuclear envelope.

The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an leaf pavement cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a leaf pavement cell fate.
The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a socket cell, a shoot epidermal cell that surrounds a trichome and provides its support.
Catalyzes the reaction: (3S)-2,3-epoxy-2,3-dihydrosqualene = camelliol C.
Catalyzes the reaction: 7-hydroxylauroyl-CoA + 3 malonyl-CoA + 2 H+ = 2-(8-hydroxy-2-oxotridecyl)-6-oxopyran-4-olate + 3 CO2 + 4 coenzyme A.
Enables the transfer of abscisic acid from one side of a membrane to the other.

label.value: trehalose biosynthesis in response to heat stress

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of trehalose that occur as a result of a heat stimulus, a temperature stimulus above the optimal temperature for that organism.

label.value: trehalose catabolism in response to heat stress

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the degradation of trehalose that occur as a result of a heat stimulus, a temperature stimulus above the optimal temperature for that organism.

A conserved protein phosphatase type 2A complex which contains a protein phosphatase type 2A, a protein phosphatase regulatory subunit, a striatin, an FHA domain protein and other subunits (at least six proteins). In fission yeast this complex negatively regulate the septation initiation network at the spindle pole body.

label.value: regulation of nematode larval development, heterochronic

value.value: Any process that modulates the consistent predetermined time point at which a nematode larva progresses from an initial condition to a later condition and the rate at which this time point is reached.

label.value: positive regulation of nematode larval development, heterochronic

value.value: Any process that modulates the consistent predetermined time point at which a nematode larva progresses from an initial condition to a later condition and increases the rate at which this time point is reached.

label.value: negative regulation of nematode larval development, heterochronic

value.value: Any process that modulates the consistent predetermined time point at which a nematode larva progresses from an initial condition to a later condition and decreases the rate at which this time point is reached.
Catalysis of the reaction: an acyl-CoA + sn-glycerol 3-phosphate = CoA + a 2-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate.
Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: glucosinolate(out) + H+(out) = glucosinolate(in) + H+(in).
The process of loading glucosinolates into the sieve tube or companion cell of the phloem for long distance transport from source to sink.
The process in which boundaries between a cotyledon and the surrounding tissue are established and maintained.
The directed movement of lithium ions (Li+) across a membrane.
The directed movement of aspartate into the vacuole across the vacuolar membrane.
The directed movement of glutamate into the vacuole across the vacuolar membrane.
The directed movement of ornithine into the vacuole across the vacuolar membrane.
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of aspartate within a cell.
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of threonine within a cell.
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of glutamate within a cell.
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of orthinine within a cell.
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of lysine within a cell.
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of histidine within a cell.
